.Dd July 10, 2026
.Dt BASE64 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm base64
.Nd encode and decode base64 data
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl di
.Op Fl w Ar columns
.Op Ar file
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
utility encodes
.Ar file ,
or the standard input if no file is specified, as base64 data and writes
the result to the standard output.
If
.Ar file
is a single dash
.Pq Sq Fl ,
.Nm
reads from the standard input.
.Pp
The options are as follows:
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Fl d , Fl -decode
Decode base64 input instead of encoding it.
.It Fl i , Fl -ignore-garbage
When decoding, ignore non-alphabet bytes instead of reporting an error.
Whitespace is always ignored while decoding.
.It Fl w Ar columns , Fl -wrap Ns = Ns Ar columns
Wrap encoded lines after
.Ar columns
characters.
The default is 76.
Use 0 to disable wrapping.
.El
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Ex -std
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr b64decode 1 ,
.Xr b64encode 1 ,
.Xr uudecode 1 ,
.Xr uuencode 1
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Nm
utility was written for
.Mx .
